530
00:41:20,842 --> 00:41:23,167
<i>But even then,</i>

531
00:41:23,167 --> 00:41:26,167
<i>you still need someone who'll tell you</i>

532
00:41:26,167 --> 00:41:28,649
<i>it's okay to be alone.</i>

533
00:41:30,788 --> 00:41:33,901
<i>Honore de Balzac.</i>

534
00:41:33,901 --> 00:41:34,823
Sorry about that.

535
00:41:34,823 --> 00:41:37,792
<i>How's your night going?</i>

536
00:41:37,792 --> 00:41:40,667
<i>If you're feeling lonely right now,</i>

537
00:41:40,667 --> 00:41:41,863
<i>I can say it for you.</i>

538
00:41:41,863 --> 00:41:43,567
That'll be 9,000 won.

539
00:41:43,567 --> 00:41:47,501
<i>That being alone is still okay.</i>

540
00:41:55,000 --> 00:41:56,777
You're back?

541
00:41:59,950 --> 00:42:01,749
Hungry, right?

542
00:42:09,033 --> 00:42:11,967
I called maintenance for the washer.

543
00:42:11,967 --> 00:42:13,861
Turns out it was broken.

544
00:42:15,942 --> 00:42:18,132
<i>It was new.</i>

545
00:42:18,933 --> 00:42:21,936
<i>My place, usually pitch-black,</i>

546
00:42:24,634 --> 00:42:26,875
<i>finally felt</i>

547
00:42:26,875 --> 00:42:29,446
<i>like it was glad</i>

548
00:42:29,446 --> 00:42:31,245
What are you doing?

549
00:42:32,393 --> 00:42:35,750
<i>- to see me.</i>
- Nice! Good call.

550
00:42:37,052 --> 00:42:39,186
Go wash up.

551
00:42:56,540 --> 00:42:57,906
How is it?

552
00:42:57,906 --> 00:42:59,607
It's delicious.

553
00:43:02,146 --> 00:43:04,176
Only "delicious"?

554
00:43:04,949 --> 00:43:06,940
Nothing else with it?

555
00:43:06,940 --> 00:43:08,783
Like what?

556
00:43:10,185 --> 00:43:12,153
Well...

557
00:43:12,153 --> 00:43:13,954
Nothing that hits the heart?

558
00:43:15,459 --> 00:43:17,425
Are you asking for praise?

559
00:43:21,496 --> 00:43:23,731
Most dishes, sure,

560
00:43:24,299 --> 00:43:25,701
but curry's different.

561
00:43:25,701 --> 00:43:27,771
It should be mostly comfortable.

562
00:43:27,771 --> 00:43:29,370
Why's that?

563
00:43:31,106 --> 00:43:33,374
Curry's my comfort food.

564
00:43:34,132 --> 00:43:37,400
Back when I was broke,
freezing, and scraping by as a musician,

565
00:43:37,400 --> 00:43:40,247
I'd grab a 1,000-won curry powder packet,

566
00:43:41,118 --> 00:43:42,968
throw in just potatoes

567
00:43:42,968 --> 00:43:47,322
and onions, make a big batch,

568
00:43:47,322 --> 00:43:48,567
and day two,

569
00:43:48,567 --> 00:43:49,901
day three,

570
00:43:49,901 --> 00:43:51,667
it tasted deeper,

571
00:43:51,667 --> 00:43:54,562
and somehow even better.

572
00:43:58,133 --> 00:44:00,067
Like it levels up overnight.

573
00:44:02,437 --> 00:44:04,873
I formed this tiny fantasy.

574
00:44:04,873 --> 00:44:06,141
What kind?

575
00:44:06,141 --> 00:44:07,775
One night,

576
00:44:09,000 --> 00:44:10,811
I come home wiped out

577
00:44:11,367 --> 00:44:14,248
for no good reason,

578
00:44:16,117 --> 00:44:18,619
and there she is, apron on,

579
00:44:19,767 --> 00:44:21,655
stirring curry,

580
00:44:22,490 --> 00:44:24,000
that smell taking over

581
00:44:24,000 --> 00:44:26,727
the entire apartment.

582
00:44:31,210 --> 00:44:33,001
Well...

583
00:44:33,001 --> 00:44:34,902
That's a pretty simple wish.

584
00:44:35,603 --> 00:44:37,805
But there's a catch.

585
00:44:39,274 --> 00:44:41,067
The wife

586
00:44:41,067 --> 00:44:44,245
has to have the apron on and nothing else.

587
00:44:45,980 --> 00:44:47,711
- Ugh, you perv.
- You'll actually do it, right?

588
00:44:47,711 --> 00:44:49,653
- Me?
- Yeah.

589
00:44:49,653 --> 00:44:52,019
You're out of your mind.

590
00:44:53,054 --> 00:44:55,534
Please make my wish come true.

591
00:44:55,534 --> 00:44:56,991
That's ridiculous.

592
00:45:06,434 --> 00:45:09,537
I've never seen you laugh this easily.

593
00:45:12,373 --> 00:45:14,509
You tagged along so I wouldn't hole up

594
00:45:14,509 --> 00:45:16,177
in my room acting all tough, right?

595
00:45:16,177 --> 00:45:18,313
Man, guiding must be such a grind.

596
00:45:18,313 --> 00:45:20,381
Not at all.

597
00:45:20,381 --> 00:45:22,150
I get to travel for free, as much as I want,

598
00:45:22,150 --> 00:45:24,686
and they pay me too. It's honestly the best.

599
00:45:24,686 --> 00:45:27,555
And the yacht ride is the most expensive add-on
in the whole package.

600
00:45:27,555 --> 00:45:29,423
Oh, really?

601
00:45:38,433 --> 00:45:41,168
Being somewhere this nice
makes me think of my husband.

602
00:45:41,885 --> 00:45:45,426
We never got around to a yacht trip together.

603
00:45:45,426 --> 00:45:47,025
You still can.

604
00:45:47,025 --> 00:45:49,476
There will be another chance.

605
00:45:50,511 --> 00:45:53,814
I lost mine too. Ten years ago.

606
00:46:08,096 --> 00:46:10,134
This tastes nothing like

607
00:46:10,134 --> 00:46:12,169
what I used to eat in Seoul.

608
00:46:12,169 --> 00:46:13,999
Try the turban shell too.

609
00:46:13,999 --> 00:46:17,200
The haenyeo ladies pulled it
from the water right here.

610
00:46:32,990 --> 00:46:35,089
"Too salty."

611
00:46:35,826 --> 00:46:37,791
"Too spicy."

612
00:46:39,096 --> 00:46:41,695
My wife used to get on me
about that all the time.

613
00:46:43,669 --> 00:46:46,734
And now the one who only ate clean
isn't here anymore.

614
00:46:47,929 --> 00:46:50,137
Funny how that works.

615
00:47:06,709 --> 00:47:08,659
Hey, look over there.

616
00:47:08,659 --> 00:47:11,617
See that group?

617
00:47:11,617 --> 00:47:12,897
Yeah.

618
00:47:12,897 --> 00:47:14,895
Keep this quiet, okay?

619
00:47:15,533 --> 00:47:19,050
Their deal is a little different.

620
00:47:19,050 --> 00:47:20,901
Different how?

621
00:47:22,010 --> 00:47:24,450
It's the "Erase-It" package.

622
00:47:24,450 --> 00:47:26,373
- Erase it?
- Shh.

623
00:47:29,711 --> 00:47:32,883
They look cheerful,

624
00:47:32,883 --> 00:47:37,217
but they're going through it.

625
00:47:39,887 --> 00:47:41,923
They picked this

626
00:47:41,923 --> 00:47:44,726
just to block it out for a bit.

627
00:47:44,726 --> 00:47:46,461
When they head home,

628
00:47:46,461 --> 00:47:50,064
real life's still waiting, exactly the same.

629
00:47:50,765 --> 00:47:53,501
But while they're here,
they want a break from all of it.

630
00:47:53,501 --> 00:47:55,634
So that's why

631
00:47:55,634 --> 00:47:57,138
they're all in the same hats.

632
00:47:57,138 --> 00:47:59,033
- Exactly.
- Got it.

633
00:47:59,033 --> 00:48:00,601
Look.

634
00:48:00,601 --> 00:48:01,901
See that pair

635
00:48:01,901 --> 00:48:03,434
in the denim shirts?

636
00:48:03,434 --> 00:48:04,212
Right there?

637
00:48:04,212 --> 00:48:06,247
- Taking pictures.
- Yeah.

638
00:48:06,247 --> 00:48:08,716
Five years married.

639
00:48:08,716 --> 00:48:10,721
Both have day jobs.

640
00:48:10,721 --> 00:48:12,033
He learned

641
00:48:12,033 --> 00:48:16,124
she'd been seeing a coworker.

642
00:48:16,124 --> 00:48:20,128
They blow up at each other pretty much daily.

643
00:48:20,128 --> 00:48:23,030
And nothing's resolved.

644
00:48:27,738 --> 00:48:28,939
See?

645
00:48:28,939 --> 00:48:31,338
They're switched to
"shut-it-off" mode right now.

646
00:48:32,901 --> 00:48:34,808
I see.

647
00:48:36,310 --> 00:48:38,167
And beside them,

648
00:48:38,167 --> 00:48:40,782
that husband backed someone,

649
00:48:40,782 --> 00:48:44,152
got wiped out, and now he's in the hole.

650
00:48:44,152 --> 00:48:46,380
The house is gone too.

651
00:48:46,380 --> 00:48:49,165
What can he even do?

652
00:48:49,165 --> 00:48:51,629
- That's so upsetting.
- Seriously.

653
00:48:51,629 --> 00:48:53,527
It really is.

654
00:48:55,797 --> 00:48:58,767
So the people over there

655
00:48:58,767 --> 00:49:01,201
have stories like that too?

656
00:49:01,739 --> 00:49:03,504
Exactly.

657
00:49:07,291 --> 00:49:08,409
Try it once.

658
00:49:08,409 --> 00:49:10,381
Huh? Try what?

659
00:49:10,381 --> 00:49:12,546
Try it.

660
00:49:15,534 --> 00:49:17,200
Ah...

661
00:49:17,200 --> 00:49:18,919
come on...

662
00:49:19,434 --> 00:49:21,255
No...

663
00:49:23,491 --> 00:49:25,211
I can't do this.

664
00:49:25,211 --> 00:49:27,694
Just say something.

665
00:49:28,365 --> 00:49:30,030
Anything works.

666
00:49:32,733 --> 00:49:34,568
That guy's

667
00:49:35,567 --> 00:49:37,934
a civil servant, desk job.

668
00:49:37,934 --> 00:49:39,725
Yeah.

669
00:49:39,725 --> 00:49:41,367
Recently, he started

670
00:49:41,367 --> 00:49:43,965
thinking about retiring

671
00:49:43,965 --> 00:49:46,814
a little early.

672
00:49:47,615 --> 00:49:50,117
And then he just pulled the plug and resigned.

673
00:49:50,117 --> 00:49:54,855
He wanted more time with his wife.

674
00:49:57,158 --> 00:49:59,159
But his wife

675
00:50:00,367 --> 00:50:02,529
got in a bad accident

676
00:50:04,832 --> 00:50:07,105
and lost an arm.

677
00:50:07,105 --> 00:50:08,194
Oh no.

678
00:50:08,194 --> 00:50:10,204
That's so cruel.

679
00:50:15,343 --> 00:50:17,377
After the accident,

680
00:50:19,133 --> 00:50:21,582
she stopped smiling.

681
00:50:26,187 --> 00:50:28,155
I think she's convinced

682
00:50:29,690 --> 00:50:32,459
there's no hope left.

683
00:50:36,399 --> 00:50:38,198
He's been

684
00:50:39,334 --> 00:50:41,300
giving up

685
00:50:41,300 --> 00:50:43,537
his time, his heart...

686
00:50:44,173 --> 00:50:46,707
everything for her.

687
00:50:48,534 --> 00:50:51,111
But he's exhausted.

688
00:50:53,514 --> 00:50:56,383
Sometimes he thinks,

689
00:50:56,973 --> 00:50:59,620
"When will this end?"

690
00:51:02,340 --> 00:51:06,059
Then he hates himself for even thinking that.

691
00:51:07,995 --> 00:51:11,367
And the reason he traveled alone is...

692
00:51:11,367 --> 00:51:13,066
Well...

693
00:51:21,449 --> 00:51:23,077
Her arm looks fine.

694
00:51:23,077 --> 00:51:24,674
Sorry?

695
00:51:28,716 --> 00:51:32,319
No one knows she wears a prosthetic arm.

696
00:51:33,220 --> 00:51:34,887
Her arm itches.

697
00:51:34,887 --> 00:51:38,625
It's like she forgets it's even prosthetic.

698
00:51:41,292 --> 00:51:43,300
Did you write this just so I'd read it?

699
00:51:43,300 --> 00:51:44,599
Huh?

700
00:51:44,599 --> 00:51:46,600
Can you even hear how this sounds?

701
00:51:48,506 --> 00:51:50,671
I mean...

702
00:51:50,671 --> 00:51:52,734
We're past the age of stupidity.

703
00:51:52,734 --> 00:51:54,408
If you'd used your phone,

704
00:51:54,408 --> 00:51:56,477
or put in even the tiniest bit of effort,

705
00:51:56,477 --> 00:51:59,947
you wouldn't have
turned in something like this.

706
00:52:01,334 --> 00:52:02,683
You know...

707
00:52:02,683 --> 00:52:05,019
When everyone else got jobs after undergrad,

708
00:52:05,019 --> 00:52:08,456
you came to grad school acting
like you had some grand academic calling.

709
00:52:08,456 --> 00:52:10,601
Honestly, I don't care.

710
00:52:10,601 --> 00:52:12,005
Yeah?

711
00:52:12,005 --> 00:52:15,896
Do you even care about your own life
and where you're headed?

712
00:52:18,389 --> 00:52:21,201
If you did, you wouldn't be doing this.

713
00:52:21,745 --> 00:52:25,239
But your poor parents must care a lot.

714
00:52:28,109 --> 00:52:29,114
Geez...

715
00:52:29,114 --> 00:52:32,679
Clueless that you're ruining your own life.

716
00:52:33,250 --> 00:52:35,782
You poor thing.

717
00:52:43,267 --> 00:52:45,135
That bastard.

718
00:52:45,626 --> 00:52:47,444
Dragging my parents into it now?

719
00:52:47,444 --> 00:52:50,331
Like he's so great.

720
00:52:50,331 --> 00:52:51,932
Why not say it to his face?

721
00:52:51,932 --> 00:52:55,025
This is straight-up disrespect.
Professor power trip stuff.

722
00:52:55,025 --> 00:52:56,334
So what?

723
00:52:56,334 --> 00:52:58,171
You're going to sue him?

724
00:53:01,378 --> 00:53:02,983
No.

725
00:53:03,614 --> 00:53:06,213
I'll rewrite it and resubmit.

726
00:53:06,984 --> 00:53:08,649
Fine.

727
00:53:13,220 --> 00:53:15,823
When do I get to meet your boyfriend?

728
00:53:15,823 --> 00:53:17,324
Why now?

729
00:53:17,324 --> 00:53:20,028
Shouldn't you two go public already?

730
00:53:20,028 --> 00:53:22,384
Like, make it official with everyone.

731
00:53:22,384 --> 00:53:23,744
You're basically living together now.

732
00:53:23,744 --> 00:53:26,300
It's not living together, I told you.

733
00:53:33,441 --> 00:53:34,578
Are you not going out?

734
00:53:34,578 --> 00:53:36,276
Pick up.

735
00:53:40,581 --> 00:53:41,943
Hi, Do Hyun.

736
00:53:41,943 --> 00:53:43,743
<i>You're finished, right?</i>

737
00:53:43,743 --> 00:53:45,357
<i>What should we do for dinner?</i>

738
00:53:45,357 --> 00:53:46,178
Dinner?

739
00:53:46,178 --> 00:53:48,289
Hyeong Jun says he's making dakbokkeumtang.

740
00:53:48,289 --> 00:53:51,225
How does that sound?

741
00:53:51,225 --> 00:53:52,938
<i>- Sorry?</i>
- No, he's...

742
00:53:52,938 --> 00:53:54,762
Let's eat together!

743
00:53:54,762 --> 00:53:57,331
- Hey.
- That sounds great.

744
00:53:57,331 --> 00:53:58,817
Is that okay?

745
00:53:58,817 --> 00:54:00,738
Please don't feel pressured to eat with them.

746
00:54:00,738 --> 00:54:02,502
He's not much of a cook.

747
00:54:03,868 --> 00:54:05,106
Lee Yeon, Ian.

748
00:54:05,106 --> 00:54:07,010
Come and eat.

749
00:54:35,936 --> 00:54:39,607
It's been ages since Jun Kyung dated anyone.

750
00:54:39,607 --> 00:54:42,467
Sometimes she feels like our eldest daughter,

751
00:54:42,467 --> 00:54:44,745
so I'm extra happy.

752
00:54:46,900 --> 00:54:48,682
I heard you make music.

753
00:54:49,166 --> 00:54:50,484
Yes.

754
00:54:50,484 --> 00:54:52,289
What kind of music do you do?

755
00:54:53,979 --> 00:54:57,824
I don't really stick to one specific genre.

756
00:54:59,160 --> 00:55:03,186
Then do you busk, like on the street?

757
00:55:04,420 --> 00:55:05,599
Well...

758
00:55:05,599 --> 00:55:07,641
if I had to label it,
it's more for film and video.

759
00:55:07,641 --> 00:55:10,803
Oh, for video.

760
00:55:11,338 --> 00:55:14,475
Anything we might recognize?

761
00:55:14,475 --> 00:55:17,210
Tell us what you've done.

762
00:55:19,434 --> 00:55:21,181
Something you'd know?

763
00:55:22,119 --> 00:55:23,217
Well...

764
00:55:23,217 --> 00:55:24,652
It doesn't have to be famous.

765
00:55:24,652 --> 00:55:27,554
Just give us anything. We'll look it up.

766
00:55:28,789 --> 00:55:30,457
Then...

767
00:55:32,167 --> 00:55:33,794
how about this?

768
00:55:34,367 --> 00:55:36,062
Do you know it?

769
00:55:46,574 --> 00:55:48,308
I know this one!

770
00:55:56,501 --> 00:55:58,085
This one has animals, right?

771
00:55:58,085 --> 00:56:00,954
They just met. How are they this close already?

772
00:56:03,093 --> 00:56:05,091
Look at you.

773
00:56:05,729 --> 00:56:07,327
What?

774
00:56:08,514 --> 00:56:10,701
You barely know each other.

775
00:56:10,701 --> 00:56:12,799
Do you like him that much?

776
00:56:14,104 --> 00:56:15,869
Yeah, I like him.

777
00:56:18,075 --> 00:56:20,501
Maybe I got my hopes up too much.

778
00:56:20,501 --> 00:56:23,110
He's not drop-dead gorgeous or anything.

779
00:56:23,110 --> 00:56:27,051
And it's not like his physique is insane.

780
00:56:27,051 --> 00:56:29,125
So what is it? What's the reason?

781
00:56:29,125 --> 00:56:32,806
Why did our worldly, ice-cold Jun Kyung

782
00:56:32,806 --> 00:56:34,921
fall this hard?

783
00:56:41,599 --> 00:56:43,664
Just because.

784
00:56:43,664 --> 00:56:44,901
Just because?

785
00:56:44,901 --> 00:56:46,033
Yeah.

786
00:56:46,033 --> 00:56:47,623
I just like him.

787
00:56:54,778 --> 00:56:55,709
Get home safe.

788
00:56:55,709 --> 00:56:57,011
- I'll get the door.
- I'm off now.

789
00:56:57,011 --> 00:56:58,309
Hyeong Jun.

790
00:56:58,309 --> 00:56:59,680
You remember what I said, right?

791
00:56:59,680 --> 00:57:01,781
Yeah, I remember.

792
00:57:02,353 --> 00:57:03,350
Bye, Jun Kyung.

793
00:57:03,350 --> 00:57:04,150
Bye.

794
00:57:04,150 --> 00:57:05,919
Bye, Do Hyun.

795
00:57:12,860 --> 00:57:14,470
So?

796
00:57:16,130 --> 00:57:18,235
I'm against this relationship.

797
00:57:18,235 --> 00:57:19,403
Why?

798
00:57:19,403 --> 00:57:22,135
You were hitting it off with Do Hyun.

799
00:57:24,142 --> 00:57:26,206
Do Hyun's too good for her.

800
00:57:26,977 --> 00:57:29,376
He's wasted on Jun Kyung.

801
00:57:29,376 --> 00:57:32,498
Honestly, I don't like it either.

802
00:57:32,498 --> 00:57:33,978
Why's that?

803
00:57:33,978 --> 00:57:35,434
Because now,

804
00:57:35,434 --> 00:57:37,985
whenever something fun happens,

805
00:57:37,985 --> 00:57:41,235
she'll tell Do Hyun first, not me.

806
00:57:41,235 --> 00:57:44,958
And when things go bad, she'll lean on Do Hyun.

807
00:57:50,062 --> 00:57:51,932
<i>To be honest,</i>

808
00:57:52,701 --> 00:57:54,668
<i>I was scared.</i>

809
00:57:55,206 --> 00:57:56,870
<i>Of what?</i>

810
00:58:00,341 --> 00:58:03,681
That I wouldn't fit in with someone like him.

811
00:58:03,681 --> 00:58:06,346
Or that he wouldn't want to fit in with me.

812
00:58:09,386 --> 00:58:11,418
Haven't I changed so much?

813
00:58:12,522 --> 00:58:14,321
No.

814
00:58:14,861 --> 00:58:17,494
You were always like that.

815
00:58:17,494 --> 00:58:20,460
You're just back to being Seo Jun Kyung.

816
00:58:24,892 --> 00:58:26,515
Really?

817
00:58:31,138 --> 00:58:32,741
What are you doing?

818
00:58:33,244 --> 00:58:35,342
You're not even changed.

819
00:58:38,979 --> 00:58:41,384
It's bedtime, and now I'm sobering up.

820
00:58:42,616 --> 00:58:45,919
I guess I got a little too excited today.

821
00:58:50,773 --> 00:58:54,027
I think today will stick with me for a while.

822
00:58:56,009 --> 00:58:58,799
It was such a good day,

823
00:58:58,799 --> 00:59:01,935
I almost feel like I don't deserve it.

824
00:59:10,334 --> 00:59:12,212
Actually...

825
00:59:14,434 --> 00:59:17,684
It hasn't been long since my mom passed away.

826
00:59:34,096 --> 00:59:35,869
I'm sorry, I didn't know.

827
00:59:58,300 --> 01:00:01,127
I take after my mom a lot.

828
01:00:03,695 --> 01:00:05,865
But toward the end,

829
01:00:07,668 --> 01:00:10,136
we really grew

830
01:00:11,004 --> 01:00:12,972
to resent each other.

831
01:00:21,048 --> 01:00:23,383
I never even got to say

832
01:00:24,501 --> 01:00:26,419
I was sorry.

833
01:00:29,467 --> 01:00:31,524
We didn't make up.

834
01:00:34,034 --> 01:00:36,096
It just ended.

835
01:00:48,133 --> 01:00:50,710
Even if you never said it,

836
01:00:53,601 --> 01:00:56,149
just carrying

837
01:01:00,234 --> 01:01:03,323
